file=AI & Agents/proto/operational/skill/proto-skill-routing.md · p—s:proto — Skill Routing (no identity layer — non-leader)=```\nidea/pilot (edge, operator, any agent) ─► agent-prototype-kit (manifest)\n└► eval-first-design (criteria, frozen) ─► registry entry (meta, state=prototype)\n└► rapid-prototyping-method (fidelity + timebox, in cage)\n└► promote-or-archive-verdict (expiry)\n├─PROMOTE─► meta (Rail 3 new-agent proposal; full house shape)\n└─ARCHIVE─► anneal (learnings ledger) + registry state change\n```\n\nHandoffs out: meta (registration, standards, governance) \· quinn (sandbox policy) \· relay (trial tool grants) \· anneal (learnings) \· gauge (missed-verdict flags) \· forge (technique-shaped hypotheses go there instead) \· edge (pilots arrive from there).\nPrecedence: expired verdicts > cage checks > new scaffolds.\n